The paper discusses computation codes in network information theory, which is a subfield of information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses distributed source coding and network coding, which are related to network information theory and could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions coding schemes, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses multiple access and distributed source coding, which could fall under cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
